A 53 km long right tributary of the river Elbe in Northern Germany. It has its source near Henstedt-Ulzburg in the village of Kisdorferwohld in Schleswig-Holstein, approximately 25 km north of Hamburg. The Alster flows roughly southwards and reaches the Elbe in Hamburg.

A populated place. A village in the district of Hinterrhein in the Swiss canton of Graubunden. An independent municipality before, it merged on 2008-01-01 with neighboring Ausserferrera to form the municipality of Ferrera.
The capital of Brazil, located in the central part of the country. Brasilia is located in the Federal District, which has the same borders as the city.

A river that rises in Rio Grande National Forest in the State of Colorado. It is formed by the confluence of several streams at the base of Canby Mountain, just east of the continental divide. From there, it flows through the San Luis Valley, then south into New Mexico through Albuquerque and Las Cruces to El Paso, Texas, where it begins to form the border between the United States and Mexico. A major tributary, the Rio Conchos, enters at Ojinaga, Chihuahua, below El Paso, and supplies most of the water in the 2,018 km Texas border segment. Other known tributaries include the Pecos and the smaller Devils, which join the Rio Grande on the site of Amistad Dam.

A department in Nicaragua. It is bordered on the north by the country of Honduras. The departments surrounding it are, Matagalpa to the south, Zelaya to the east, and Esteli, Madriz, and Nueva Segovia.
The administrative centre of the municipality of Baerum in Norway, and declared itself a city on 2003-06-04.

A populated place. and former municipality in Akershus county, Norway. It bordered Ostfold county to the south, Hedmark county to the north and Sweden to the east. It was created by a split from Holand municipality on 1905-01-01. On 1966-01-01 Setskog was merged with Nordre Holand, Sondre Hpland and Aurskog to form the new municipality Aurskog-Holand.

One of the major rivers of Spain and Portugal. It forms part of the border between the two countries. It is 778 km long and drains an area of about 67,000 km2. It flows into the Gulf of Cadiz, part of the Atlantic Ocean.

A river in Central Europe. It begins in the Czech Republic and flows through western Poland, later forming the northern 187 km of the border between Poland and Germany, part of the Oder-Neisse line. The river ultimately flows into the Szczecin Lagoon north of Szczecin and then into three branches (Dziwna, Swina and Peene) that empty into the Baltic Sea.
A river. A tributary of the Ticino River.
A populated place. A former municipality, incorporated into the Municipality of Ringgenberg in 1853.

One of the largest rivers in Switzerland. The Reuss, the Aar, and the Limmat come together near Brugg. After the confluence the river continues as the Aar, which flows into the Rhine, which runs through Germany into the North Sea. Rising in the Gotthard massif, the Reuss runs from the Urserental to the Aare. It runs through Lake Lucerne, where a pioneering needle dam (just upstream from the Spreuerbrucke) maintains the water level. The Reuss continues through the Schollenen Gorge and under the Devil's Bridge at St. Gotthard Pass before joining the Aare near Windisch.
A populated place. A village in the canton of Berne, Switzerland. The former municipality of the district of Thun merged with Forst on 2007-01-01 to form Forst-Langenbuhl.

A former municipality in the district of Blenio in the canton of Ticino in Switzerland. On 2005-01-25, the cantonal authorities announced that Ghirone would merge with Aquila, Campo Blenio, Olivone and Torre to form a new municipality to be called Blenio. This union was carried through on 2006-10-22.

A former municipality in the district of Blenio in the canton of Ticino in Switzerland. On 2005-01-25, the cantonal authorities announced that Aquila would merge with Campo Blenio, Ghirone, Olivone and Torre to form a new municipality to be called Blenio. This union was carried through on 2006-10-22.
A river in the Grisons canton, eastern Switzerland. It is a tributary of the Albula river, which it meets in Tiefencastel.

A river in the Swiss canton of Ticino. The springs are near the Cristallina mountain and the river runs through the Val Sambuco, the Val Lavizzara, and the Valle Maggia, and enters Lago Maggiore between Ascona and Locarno. The village Maggia is situated on the river. The river is used for hydroelectric power production, e.g. with the dams of Lago del Naret and Lago del Sambuco near the sources.
A river in the Schachental; on leaving the valley, the Schachen flows past Altdorf and joins the Reuss at Attinghausen.

A river whose source is in Fontibre (Cantabria). It flows through cities such as Miranda de Ebro, Logrono, Zaragoza, Flix, Tortosa, and Amposta before discharging in a delta on the Mediterranean Sea in the province of Tarragona.
One of the governorates of Egypt. It is in the south of the country along the Nile. Its capital is Luxor.
A department in Paraguay. The capital is Ciudad del Este (formerly known as Ciudad Presidente Stroessner).
A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of Pedro Juan Caballero.
A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of Salto del Guaira.

A department in Paraguay. The capital is Aregua. Bounded: North: the departments of Cordillera and Presidente Hayes; West: Argentina separated by the Paraguay River; East: the department of Paraguari; South: the department of Neembucu.

A department in the western region of Paraguay. It is the country's largest department. In 1992 the department Nueva Asuncion was merged with Boqueron, effectively recreating the departement as of 1945 when it was split, and the capital was moved from Doctor Pedro P. Pena to Filadelfia.
A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of Caacupe.
A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of San Juan Bautista.
A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of Paraguari.
A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of Villa Hayes.
A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of Caazapa.
A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of Encarnacion.

A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of San Pedro. Its limits are: To the North: the Ypane River, which separates San Pedro from Concepcion - To the South: Manduvira River and Hondo Stream, which separates it from Cordillera; also San Joaquin Cordillera, which limits with Caaguazu - To the East: Aguaray River, the limit with Amambay, and the rivers Jejui Guazu, Curuguaty and Corrientes, which separates San Pedro from Canindeyu - To the West: the Paraguay River, natural limit with Presidente Hayes.
A department in Paraguay. The capital is the city of Pilar.
A department of Paraguay. The capital is the city of Concepcion.
A department in Paraguay. In 1992 the Chaco Department was merged with Alto Paraguay, effectively recreating the original department Olimpo as it existed until 1945.
A department in Nicaragua. The capital is Juigalpa.
